# HireHub - Full-Stack Job Portal

A production-ready full-stack job portal built with Next.js, TypeScript, Prisma, and MySQL. This project demonstrates modern web development practices including authentication, role-based access control, AI agent integration, and Docker deployment.

## 🚀 Features

### Core Features
- **User Authentication**: Secure login/register with JWT tokens
- **Role-Based Access Control**: Admin, Moderator, and User roles
- **Job Management**: Full CRUD operations for job postings
- **Application System**: Apply to jobs and track application status
- **Search & Filter**: Advanced job search with filters
- **Pagination**: Efficient data loading across all endpoints
- **AI Agent Integration**: Smart job recommendations and auto-apply functionality

### Security Features
- **Password Hashing**: bcrypt for secure password storage
- **JWT Authentication**: Token-based authentication with 7-day expiry
- **Input Validation**: Zod schema validation on all endpoints
- **Rate Limiting**: Protects against brute force attacks
- **Security Headers**: XSS, CSRF, and clickjacking protection
- **SQL Injection Prevention**: Parameterized queries via Prisma

### Architecture
- **Frontend**: Next.js 16 with React 19 and TypeScript
- **Backend**: Next.js API Routes with RESTful design
- **Database**: MySQL 8 with Prisma ORM
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Deployment**: Docker with docker-compose

## 📋 Requirements

- Node.js 18+
- MySQL 8+
- npm or yarn

## 🛠️ Installation

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd hirehub
```

### 2. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Set up environment variables
Create a `.env` file in the root directory:

```env
DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:password@localhost:3306/hirehub"
JWT_SECRET="your-secret-key-here"
```

### 4. Set up the database
```bash
# Run Prisma migrations
npx prisma migrate dev --name init

# Generate Prisma client
npx prisma generate
```

### 5. Run the development server
```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

## 🐳 Docker Deployment

### Using Docker Compose

1. Build and start the 3-service stack (`frontend`, `backend`, `db`):
```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

2. Services:
- Frontend: `http://localhost:3000`
- Backend API: `http://localhost:3001`
- OpenAPI JSON: `http://localhost:3001/api/openapi`

3. To stop the containers:
```bash
docker-compose down
```

### Manual Docker Build

1. Build the image:
```bash
docker build -t hirehub .
```

2. Run the container:
```bash
docker run -p 3001:3001 --env-file .env hirehub
```

## 📚 API Documentation

### Authentication

#### Register
```http
POST /api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "John Doe"
}
```

#### Login
```http
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
```

### Jobs

#### List Jobs
```http
GET /api/jobs?page=1&limit=10&search=developer&type=FULL_TIME
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

#### Create Job
```http
POST /api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Senior Developer",
  "description": "Job description...",
  "salary": 100000,
  "location": "Remote",
  "type": "FULL_TIME"
}
```

#### Get Job
```http
GET /api/jobs/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

#### Update Job
```http
PUT /api/jobs/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "status": "CLOSED"
}
```

#### Delete Job
```http
DELETE /api/jobs/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Applications

#### List Applications
```http
GET /api/applications?page=1&limit=10&status=PENDING
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

#### Create Application
```http
POST /api/applications
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jobId": 1,
  "coverLetter": "I am interested in this position..."
}
```

#### Update Application Status
```http
PUT /api/applications/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ACCEPTED"
}
```

#### Delete Application
```http
DELETE /api/applications/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Users (Admin Only)

#### List Users
```http
GET /api/users?page=1&limit=10&role=USER
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

#### Update User Role
```http
PUT /api/users/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "ADMIN"
}
```

#### Delete User
```http
DELETE /api/users/:id
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### AI Agent

#### Get Job Recommendations
```http
POST /api/agent/recommend
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "skills": "javascript, react, typescript",
  "preferences": "remote, full-time",
  "salaryMin": 80000
}
```

#### Auto-Apply to Jobs
```http
POST /api/agent/auto-apply
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "criteria": {
    "keywords": "developer, engineer",
    "minSalary": 80000,
    "jobTypes": ["FULL_TIME", "REMOTE"]
  },
  "limit": 3
}
```

## 🗄️ Database Schema

### Tables

#### Users
- `id` (Primary Key)
- `email` (Unique)
- `password` (Hashed)
- `name` (Optional)
- `role` (USER, ADMIN, MODERATOR)
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`

#### Jobs
- `id` (Primary Key)
- `title`
- `description` (Text)
- `salary`
- `location` (Optional)
- `type` (FULL_TIME, PART_TIME, CONTRACT, INTERNSHIP, REMOTE)
- `status` (ACTIVE, CLOSED, DRAFT)
- `employerId` (Foreign Key → Users)
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`

#### Applications
- `id` (Primary Key)
- `status` (PENDING, ACCEPTED, REJECTED, UNDER_REVIEW)
- `coverLetter` (Text, Optional)
- `userId` (Foreign Key → Users)
- `jobId` (Foreign Key → Jobs)
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`

### Relationships
- Users → Jobs (One-to-Many)
- Users → Applications (One-to-Many)
- Jobs → Applications (One-to-Many)

## 🔐 Security Features

### Authentication & Authorization
- JWT-based authentication with 7-day token expiry
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Protected routes on both frontend and backend

### Input Validation
- Zod schema validation on all API endpoints
- Email format validation
- Password strength requirements (min 6 characters)

### Rate Limiting
- Auth endpoints: 5 requests per 15 minutes per IP
- General endpoints: 100 requests per 15 minutes per IP
- Rate limit headers included in responses

### Security Headers
- X-Frame-Options: DENY
- X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
- X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
- Content-Security-Policy
- Strict-Transport-Security (production)

### Data Protection
- Passwords hashed with bcrypt (salt rounds: 10)
- SQL injection prevention via Prisma ORM
- XSS protection through input sanitization

## 🤖 AI Agent Integration

The AI Agent provides two main features:

### 1. Job Recommendations
Analyzes user's application history and preferences to recommend relevant jobs. Uses:
- Keyword matching in job titles and descriptions
- Salary preferences
- Job type preferences
- Application history analysis
- Competition scoring (fewer applications = higher score)

### 2. Auto-Apply
Automatically applies to jobs matching user criteria:
- Keyword-based job search
- Salary range filtering
- Job type filtering
- Location filtering
- Configurable limit on applications per run

